    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In plaster, the appearance of small, cone-shaped holes up to a quarter inch in diameter; caused by the expansion of lime or foreign material and occurring between three months and up to one year after the plaster has set.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
